# Python Standards

## Data Validation & Config

- Use `pydantic.BaseModel` for all data structures crossing module boundaries
- Use `pydantic_settings.BaseSettings` for configuration loaded from `.env`
- Validate API responses with Pydantic models before storing

## HTTP & Async

- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` for all Polygon API calls
- Prefer `async/await` for I/O-bound work; use `asyncio.gather` for parallel fetches
- Always set reasonable timeouts (`httpx.Timeout(30.0)`)
- Handle pagination: follow `next_url` until exhausted

## SQLAlchemy 2.0

- Declarative models with `mapped_column` (not legacy `Column`)
- Use `AsyncSession` for database operations
- Repository pattern: one repository class per domain entity
- Never construct raw SQL strings — use the ORM or `text()` with bound params

## Error Handling

```python
class OptionFinderError(Exception): ...
class PolygonAPIError(OptionFinderError): ...
class ScoringError(OptionFinderError): ...
class AlertError(OptionFinderError): ...
```

- Catch specific exceptions; never bare `except:`
- Log the exception with context before re-raising or wrapping

## Logging

- `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)` at module top
- Include structured context: `logger.info("scored", extra={"ticker": ..., "score": ...})`

## Testing

- pytest with `pytest-asyncio` for async tests
- Fixtures in `conftest.py` per module
- Mock all external I/O (Polygon API, SMTP, database) in unit tests
